Package: mismeasured
Type: Package
Title: SIMEX and MC-SIMEX Correction for Measurement Error and Misclassification
Version: 0.2.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Maciej", "Beresewicz", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           email = "maciej.beresewicz@ue.poznan.pl",
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-8281-4301")),
    person("Helmut", "Kuechenhoff", role = "ctb"))
Description: High-performance Simulation-Extrapolation (SIMEX) and Misclassification
    SIMEX (MC-SIMEX) for correcting measurement error and misclassification bias in
    generalized linear models. Uses a formula interface with 'me()' and 'mc()' terms
    inspired by 'brms' to specify error-prone variables inline. The simulation step
    uses compiled C++ code via 'Rcpp' and 'RcppEigen' for fast IRLS fitting (~100-300x
    speedup). Implements both the standard MC-SIMEX (Kuechenhoff et al., 2006,
    <doi:10.1111/j.1541-0420.2005.00396.x>) and the improved exact-correction method
    (Sevilimedu and Yu, 2026, <doi:10.1002/sim.70418>). Based on Cook and Stefanski
    (1994) <doi:10.1080/01621459.1994.10476871>.
